==Finnish==

===Etymology 1===
Presumably from earlier ''*vapada'', from {{etyl|sla-pro|fi}} {{m|sla-pro|*sveboda}}.

====Pronunciation====
* {{fi-IPA}}
* {{rhymes|ɑpɑː|lang=fi}}
* {{hyphenation|va|paa|lang=fi}}

====Adjective====
{{fi-adj||vapaampi|vapain}}

# [[free]] (''not imprisoned or enslaved'')
#: ''Olen '''vapaa''' mies.''
#:: I am a '''free''' man.
# free (''unconstrained'')
#: ''Hänelle annettiin '''vapaat''' kädet tehdä, mitä hän haluaa.''
#:: He was given '''free''' rein to do whatever he wanted.
# free (''released'')
#: ''Päästimme kanin '''vapaaksi'''.''
#:: We set the rabbit '''free'''.
# free, [[off]] (''without obligations'')
#: ''Voit pitää loppupäivän '''vapaata'''.''
#:: You can take the rest of the day '''off'''.
# [[spare]], free (''not filled with activity or work'')
#: ''Minulla on paljon '''vapaa'''-aikaa.''
#:: I have a lot of '''free''' time.
# [[vacant]]
#: ''Istuin on '''vapaa'''.''
#:: The seat is '''vacant'''.
# [[unmarried]], [[single]]
# [[free-range]] (of, pertaining to, or produced by animals that are allowed to roam freely, rather than being confined indoors)
#: ''Ostan aina '''vapaan''' kanan munia.''
#:: I always buy '''free-range''' eggs.

